p.m:
\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \frac{2}{9} + \frac{11}{18}
        \amp = \frac{4}{18} + \frac{11}{18} \\
        \amp = \frac{4 + 11}{18} \\
        \amp = \frac{15}{18} \amp  \hbox{We can reduce this by dividing 3 into both the numerator and the denominator.}\\
        \amp = \frac{5}{6}
\end{aligned}
    }
